1
00:00:01,480 --> 00:00:02,480
Nice.

2
00:00:03,560 --> 00:00:06,720
Weird.
-Why? It's nice to break the routine a bit.

3
00:00:08,039 --> 00:00:10,120
I'll say it's nice when we're on our way back home.

4
00:00:10,680 --> 00:00:12,280
Listen, it was a complicated week,

5
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:14,680
what’s it like taking Mom and Dad
out to dinner on a Friday?

6
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:17,280
It's like pulling a wisdom tooth from a stubborn person.

7
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:19,400
Yeah, I don’t get why they’re so glued to home.

8
00:00:19,480 --> 00:00:21,080
Like two turtles.
-Yeah.

9
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:24,800
Speaking of being glued at home,
you’re not exactly a free spirit yourself.

10
00:00:25,360 --> 00:00:28,600
What are you comparing? I don’t really have anywhere to go,

11
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:30,120
mainly I don’t have anyone to go with.

12
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,840
Okay, you need to think about what came first,

13
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:33,920
the fact that you don’t have anyone to go with, so you don’t go out,

14
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:36,400
or you don’t go out because you don’t have anyone.

15
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:37,880
Isn’t there a third option?

16
00:00:37,960 --> 00:00:39,720
There is, but I don’t want to offend anyone.

17
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,440
Hey, have you ever thought about writing questions

18
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:43,200
for the psychometric exam?
-Of course.

19
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:47,480
A couple goes out to a restaurant on Friday
night to celebrate their anniversary.

20
00:00:47,680 --> 00:00:52,000
Meanwhile, a turtle leaves Binyamina, who will arrive first?

21
00:00:53,240 --> 00:00:56,600
Why don’t you take the girls tomorrow
to the turtle bridge at Alexander Stream?

22
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:58,320
It’s going to be a really nice weekend.

23
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,600
Oh, oh, Moroccan,

24
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:01,560
are you planning to take the girls to the turtle bridge?

25
00:01:02,040 --> 00:01:04,200
Seriously, I’m not leaving the house day after day.

26
00:01:04,280 --> 00:01:06,760
So don’t make suggestions, no turtles, no stress.

27
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:10,200
Anyway, tomorrow they’re going to Grandpa Pinchas,
he looks like a turtle himself.

28
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:12,160
Do you think Shai will manage?

29
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:14,960
Shai? You mean the driver of Mr. Miss Daisy?

30
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:18,560
Could you please close the window? I’m cold.

31
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:20,120
Of course, ma'am.
-Wow, wow, wow...

32
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:22,680
What’s this supposed to be? What, do you want to suffocate me?

33
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:24,440
Okay, look, close that window

34
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:26,920
and open that one.

35
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:29,800
And turn on the heat.

36
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,040
Mom.

37
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,840
Look at me, look at me and...

38
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:52,920
Do me a favor, next time I travel,
remind me to leave a quarter of an hour early

39
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:56,920
to adjust the seat back to my size and shape.

40
00:01:58,040 --> 00:01:58,920
What happened?

41
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:01,880
They’re building wide roads here.

42
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,280
Why did we even have to go out?

43
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,360
What, can’t we do this at home?

44
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:08,479
Trust me, a bottle of wine would have been enough.
-True.

45
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:11,840
Believe me.
-Really, come on, what’s this? They want to celebrate you,

46
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,240
your kids want to pamper you,

47
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:16,960
Orna booked a spot at an amazing bistro,
it has great reviews.

48
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:18,520
Ben, boy
Benny

49
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,080
What happened?

50
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,560
The windshield, if you want to clean it,

51
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:28,280
you need to do it from the outside
because the sprayer isn’t working.

52
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:31,280
Forget it, forget it, the high beams are too bright.

53
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:36,040
Hey Shai, what’s this heat about?
-It’s on grill.

54
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:39,160
Want me to put on some music?
-The radio isn’t working.

55
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,080
Should I sing?

56
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,080
No.
-No.

57
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,400
And let’s go out a bit

58
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:47,440
the night was pale

59
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:51,520
in the expanses...

60
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:55,560
the lights.

61
00:02:56,560 --> 00:03:02,360
And you were here without him passing by.

62
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,560
Are you sure about those words?
-Yeah.

63
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:10,120
"The jackal howled because he had no food."

64
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,080
May the name save us.

65
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:22,120
Hadar, we thought you wouldn't make it.
-No, here we are, all good.

66
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:24,720
I'm Gal, the shift manager.

67
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:26,920
Where... I spoke with Orna?

68
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,080
Yes, yes, I'm back, Orna is the older sister.

69
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:33,120
I'm Meirav, the younger sister,
the one who still hasn't left home.

70
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:36,560
Nice to meet you, I hope everyone is out and on their way.
-Yeah, yeah.

71
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:39,440
Is there a problem?
-No, no, God forbid, there's no problem,

72
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:41,080
It's just that when I booked the VIP room

73
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:43,440
I told you, it's yours until 8:30 PM,

74
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:46,040
after that, I have a very important event here.

75
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:48,920
What, are you implying ours isn't important?

76
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,000
No, no, of course not,

77
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:52,880
I'm just saying I can't
be flexible about this.

78
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:56,280
And on other days, is there room for flexibility?

79
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:01,880
Well, if you'll excuse me,
I have a few important things to sort out in the kitchen.

80
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:08,680
Cute.

81
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:12,920
So authoritative.
-Yeah.

82
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,920
And was there a client there?

83
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:18,519
The wine and the glass are here with me.
-Okay.

84
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:23,120
Is it still a long drive?
-No, just five minutes.

85
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:26,600
Silvan, what's that red light on the dashboard?

86
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:29,000
What, is it Aladin's light?
-What, is it out of oil?

87
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:30,640
Hit the dashboard.

88
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,720
No, at the air conditioning vent.

89
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:34,040
Not at...

90
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:35,720
Your side, over there.

91
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:38,120
Okay?
-Yeah.

92
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:41,600
But isn't that dangerous?
-No, what's dangerous?

93
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:43,440
Sali arranged for a car to run without oil,

94
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:45,120
it's a low-fat car.

95
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:49,240
Why the insistence that the parents arrive after everyone?

96
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:50,480
It's not a surprise.

97
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:52,400
Oh, right, but I think it would be nice for them to arrive

98
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:54,800
and everyone shouts "Congratulations." Nice.

99
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:55,920
Let it be.

100
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:58,080
I'm starving, where is everyone really?

101
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,160
Manny has a new baby, cool,

102
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:02,880
but where are Orna and Moshe?
And she even booked the place.

103
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,080
Right, you're absolutely right.

104
00:05:04,760 --> 00:05:06,640
Here comes the cute authoritative one.

105
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:09,680
Is everything okay?
-They're on their way,

106
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:12,760
we're just a family that
is always late.

107
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:16,840
The family just isn't used
to leaving the house, so there's a bit of pressure.

108
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:19,920
But don't worry, everything settles down after the food,

109
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:23,520
which is 13 minutes after it's served.
-I get it.

110
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,440
-Not really.

111
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,160
Orna, honey, where are you?

112
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:31,560
Come on, hurry up,
in a minute they'll kick us out of the restaurant.

113
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:34,240
From the bistro, all good.

114
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:37,200
I understand that's

115
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:40,760
so tell Moshe to take a detour
barely any traffic light and just get here.

116
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:43,080
Do you have family coming from the far south?

117
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:45,840
No, they live in a Yemenite moshav, Moshe.

118
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:48,760
I don't know them but it sounds Zionist.

119
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:52,920
Hey, are you by any chance looking for a shift supervisor?
-No.

120
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:55,160
No, thanks.

121
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:57,920
But where are you guys now?
-No, no. Why did we leave here?

122
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,160
And just so you know, the next exit
is only seven kilometers away.

123
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:03,160
And my parents live ten minutes from the restaurant in Kfar Saba.

124
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,920
Honey, do me a favor, hurry up.

125
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,040
Ten minutes.

126
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,360
Really.

127
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:10,120
Since when do we have a private jet
that you measure in a straight line?

128
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:12,360
My parents are about to get there,
there’s a lot of pressure at the bistro,

129
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,600
and you’re taking us on a trip south.

130
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,160
But I’m telling you, the signage is terrible.

131
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,600
How can you understand where to turn here?
-Of course, terrible signage,

132
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:20,400
but for some reason, it only happens to you, right?

133
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,560
You think all those people driving ahead of us
aren’t making mistakes, of course?

134
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,480
They actually look pretty confident in their way.

135
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:27,440
Believe me, you look confident to them too.
-Yeah, really very confident.

136
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,920
You’re such a fool.

137
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:34,080
Hey, do you think you stressed out the cute guy?

138
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:37,200
I need to stall my parents.
-I need to change my approach.

139
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:43,440
(Unintelligible)

140
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:45,600
Are you managing with them?
-Yeah, yeah.

141
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:48,960
Oh, like you can’t expand.
-Yeah.

142
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:51,800
So you’re only answering me with yes or no now?
-Yeah.

143
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,960
Are you really suffering?
-Yeah.

144
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,840
(Unintelligible)

145
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:56,800
Give it to me.

146
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:01,360
Hello, honey.
-Hey, Mom, congratulations.

147
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,760
What’s going on?

148
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:04,680
Look, I’m not sure we’ll make it today.

149
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:06,240
Why, what happened?
-I don’t know,

150
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,640
the lights on the clock board keep flashing,

151
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:11,840
I feel like I’m in a cash cab
with all the blinking lights.

152
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,920
I told Dad we need to sell this antique,

153
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,840
he insists on fixing the old clunker.

154
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,080
Mom, can you give Shai back to me for a second?

155
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:19,640
Okay, but make it quick
because he’s on the phone,

156
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,000
the hands-free is broken too.

157
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,480
Oh, honey.
-Honey, listen for a second,

158
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:26,080
just no one has arrived yet,

159
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:30,080
so I need you to stall them
just a tiny bit, okay? Just a little.

160
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,720
But, what...
-Try to calm them down,

161
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:33,000
I don’t know, play them some music.

162
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:35,240
No, the radio’s broken too, I’m singing to them.

163
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:38,480
It’s a great car.
-It was. Ten weeks ago.

164
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:39,720
It was a great car.

165
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:41,440
"Take a break

166
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:44,200
and don’t think..."
-In the meantime

167
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,400
"just go out

168
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:49,160
to the street..."

169
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,120
Okay, he’s stalling them, I hope.

170
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:55,400
What’s wrong with you? What are you doing?

171
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:58,160
Okay, how do you want me to be, like this?

172
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:03,360
Hasn’t anyone arrived yet?
-No. Look, I’m talking to them,

173
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:05,040
they’re really, really close.

174
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:06,320
Come on, really, Galchuk...

175
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:08,520
No need for equipment, just a wave is fine.

176
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,000
How close are they?

177
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:12,680
Shabbat Shalom.
-This close.

178
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:15,200
This is Orna, the sister you talked to.

179
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,480
Hi, Shabbat Shalom.

180
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:18,400
And this is Moshe, her husband, a tour guide.

181
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,200
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

182
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:23,040
I'll send you a waiter.
-Really?

183
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:26,320
Here’s a fix, wait, a waitress to take the order.

184
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:30,600
So, how was the trip? Did you see an alpaca?

185
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,159
Look, we ended up being the first ones here.

186
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:34,159
What was the deal? Hey! Are you sure you didn’t get lost?

187
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,480
But just as we were about to enter
we suddenly saw the bistro sign.

188
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,120
I'm great at getting confused.
-Yeah, for sure.

189
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,480
Where are Manny and Alin?
-Hold on, I'm calling him now.

190
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:45,200
What, flirting with the manager?

191
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:47,480
No way.
-No way.

192
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,280
What's up, Manny, where are you guys?

193
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,960
Shani, what's the rush, have they arrived yet?

194
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,560
No, but everyone else is here except you.

195
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:54,760
If you plan to be late, you better turn around!

196
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:56,880
Why does the manager need this room at 8:30?

197
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:59,560
Well, we got held up because of the kid,
he had a stomach ache, diarrhea,

198
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:00,680
all the mess came out.

199
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:02,800
Okay, Manny, spare me the details.

200
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:05,600
And about the owner, tell him
it's been 13 minutes and the food is behind us.

201
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:08,240
Manny, get here right away and no third-grade excuses.

202
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,240
But Manny...

203
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:13,560
Fine, I didn’t want to tell her
I got stuck in the bathroom.

204
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:15,600
How long are you going to use Sivan
for your excuses?

205
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,800
How long will this last, a year, a year and a half?

206
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,840
So, what then?
-When he grows up, we'll have another one.

207
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:21,200
You’ll have another one.

208
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:25,320
I'm sorry, babe, Shani just stresses me out.

209
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:27,760
What, is she nervous?
-No, just acting tough.

210
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:30,600
You're really tough today.
-Yeah, I'm sorry,

211
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:33,240
but they're in the car with the parents,
I've been holding them up for hours.

212
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:34,640
They have car troubles.

213
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:37,160
He's already singing them old Israeli songs
part seven,

214
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:39,000
So you want me to stay calm?

215
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:41,360
Okay, fine, you're right, it's stressful,
but do me a favor, Shani.

216
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:43,120
Shani, Shani,

217
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:47,600
Someone once told me that to relax,
to relieve stress,

218
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:49,360
it's good to tell or hear a joke,

219
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:51,920
it's something! Biological that releases endorphins,

220
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:55,360
the brain laughs and it works on the nervous system.

221
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,440
Does anyone have a joke?

222
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:59,960
Alright, I'll tell one.

223
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:02,320
I'll tell one, I actually have a current joke.

224
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:09,480
Two guys at a restaurant conference, they order a waitress.

225
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:14,120
-What’s that?...

226
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,840
They're hungry, they order a waitress, two guys.

227
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:21,040
Hello again, everyone.

228
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:23,120
You said you’d send a waitress,

229
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:24,480
did you miss us?

230
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:27,280
They're all busy, I'll take everyone's order.

231
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,200
Yeah, the problem is not everyone has arrived yet.

232
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:34,120
I have an idea. Why don’t you call them,
ask each one what they want to eat,

233
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,360
and that way, when they arrive, the dishes will be ready.

234
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:37,840
Orna, take care of this.

235
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:41,560
I just noticed, this is the regular menu.

236
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:45,800
Do you have a business menu?
-No.

237
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,840
Am I in a joke? You're really making me laugh now.

238
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:50,120
Shani, what’s going on?
We’ve been driving around for hours.

239
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:52,400
Babe, babe, just drive around with them a bit longer, come on.

240
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:54,200
It’s just that Manny and Alin haven’t arrived yet.

241
